      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "5cec5ea20d35e630",
      "text": "When eventually the erring Fulani gets arrested, he would be threatened with prosecution for destroying farms, armed robbery, possession of dangerous weapons etc. and such threats would lead to the Fulani parting with money (or cows) to settle the police[Albert;2010:p102]. Once this was done, the police would advise the complainant and the Fulani to go and settle their misunderstanding amicably. The farmer would be advised not to harass the Fulani and if he (the complainant) proved stubborn, the table could be turned against him. This situation made the farmers to have little or no confidence in the police, hence, they usually resorted to self –help."
